---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const linkPrimary =
  'inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-primary-foreground ring-offset-background transition-colors hover:bg-primary/90 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2';
const linkSecondary =
  'inline-flex h-10 items-center justify-center rounded-md border border-input bg-background px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium ring-offset-background transition-colors hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2';
---

<Layout
  title="Invite-only check-in your client can put their name on"
  description="Private RSVPs, tiered guest lists, and door ops for brand activations. Their branding, your control, no ticketing platform in the room."
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-background text-foreground">

    {/* Nav */}
    <nav class="sticky top-0 z-50 border-b border-border bg-background/90 backdrop-blur-sm">
      <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-6xl items-center justify-between px-6 py-4">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight">AizuPass</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">/ Agencies</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <a href="/login" class="text-sm text-muted-foreground transition-colors hover:text-foreground">
            Sign in
          </a>
          <a href="/signup" class={linkPrimary}>
            Request access
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <main>

      {/* Hero */}
      <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pb-16 pt-20 text-center">
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">
          For agencies & brand activations
        </p>
        <h1 class="mb-6 text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
          Invite-only check-in<br />your client can put their name on.
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mb-10 max-w-2xl text-xl text-muted-foreground">
          Private RSVPs, tiered guest lists, and door ops for brand activations.
          Their branding. Your control. No ticketing platform in the room.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-3 sm:flex-row">
          <a href="/signup" class={linkPrimary + ' px-8 py-3 text-base'}>
            Request access
          </a>
          <a href="#features" class={linkSecondary + ' px-8 py-3 text-base'}>
            See features
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">White-label ready · Offline-capable · Audit trails</p>
      </section>

      {/* Tagline bar */}
      <div class="border-y border-border bg-muted/40 py-5 text-center">
        <p class="text-base font-medium tracking-wide text-foreground">
          RSVP, tiers, and check-in — your client on every surface.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Core value props */}
      <section id="features" class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-20">
        <div class="grid gap-12">

          {/* Feature 1 */}
          <div class="grid items-center gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div>
              <div class="mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-2xl">
                🎨
              </div>
              <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Client-branded from invite to door.</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                Logo, colors, custom domain. The experience reads as their event, not a third-party tool.
                No "Powered by Eventbrite" anywhere your client's eye lands.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/30 p-6">
              <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">What guests see</p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg bg-background p-3">
                  <span class="text-lg">📧</span>
                  <span class="text-muted-foreground">Invitation from <span class="font-semibold text-foreground">client@brand.com</span></span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg bg-background p-3">
                  <span class="text-lg">📱</span>
                  <span class="text-muted-foreground">Check-in at <span class="font-semibold text-foreground">rsvp.clientbrand.com</span></span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center gap-3 rounded-lg bg-background p-3">
                  <span class="text-lg">✅</span>
                  <span class="text-muted-foreground">QR code with their logo, not ours</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Feature 2 */}
          <div class="grid items-center gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="order-2 sm:order-1 rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/30 p-6">
              <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">Tiered access</p>
              <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg bg-background p-3">
                  <span class="font-medium text-foreground">VIP Early Access</span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Green dot</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg bg-background p-3">
                  <span class="font-medium text-foreground">General Admission</span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Standard</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg bg-background p-3">
                  <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Press + Media</span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Photo icon</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between rounded-lg bg-background p-3">
                  <span class="font-medium text-foreground">Staff + Production</span>
                  <span class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">All-access</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="order-1 sm:order-2">
              <div class="mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-2xl">
                🎟️
              </div>
              <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Control who gets in.</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                Tiered lists (VIP / GA / press / staff). Approval/deny flows. Capacity caps.
                Plus-ones that follow rules. No public listing, ever.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          {/* Feature 3 */}
          <div class="grid items-center gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div>
              <div class="mb-4 flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-2xl">
                📊
              </div>
              <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight">Post-event proof in the recap.</h3>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">
                Check-in timestamps, headcount, completion rate, tier breakdown.
                Built-in ops metrics that belong in your deck — no manual counting required.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-muted/30 p-6">
              <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">Sample recap metrics</p>
              <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-center">
                <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-4">
                  <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">487</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Total check-ins</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-4">
                  <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">94%</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Completion rate</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-4">
                  <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">1.8s</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Median scan time</p>
                </div>
                <div class="rounded-lg bg-background p-4">
                  <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-foreground">7:15 PM</p>
                  <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Peak arrival</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      {/* More features grid */}
      <section class="border-t border-border bg-muted/30 py-20">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
          <h2 class="mb-12 text-center text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Built for agency ops</h2>
          <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2">

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-xl">
                👥
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Multiple staff, one view</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Assign door scanners, each in their lane. Real-time sync when online; offline queue when the venue's network is what it always is.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-xl">
                🔒
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Their data. Your account. No platform in between.</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Guest data doesn't feed someone else's marketing. Export clean CSVs for your CRM. Move it anywhere when the activation ends.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-xl">
                ⚡
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Offline when you need it</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Basements. Rooftops. Convention halls. The scanner queues check-ins locally and syncs when connection returns.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="flex gap-4">
              <div class="flex h-10 w-10 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary/10 text-xl">
                🔍
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="mb-1 font-semibold">Manual fallback</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">QR won't scan? Search by name or email. One-tap check-in. Atomic operations mean no double entries even with multiple scanners.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Pricing */}
      <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-20">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-center text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Agency-friendly pricing</h2>
        <p class="mb-12 text-center text-muted-foreground">Invoice-ready. No per-attendee fees. White-label on Business.</p>
        <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-background p-6">
            <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">Pro</p>
            <p class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold">$39<span class="text-lg font-normal text-muted-foreground">/mo</span></p>
            <ul class="mb-6 space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
              <li>✓ Unlimited activations + guests</li>
              <li>✓ Unlimited staff scanners</li>
              <li>✓ Custom logo + colors</li>
              <li>✓ CSV export for recaps</li>
              <li class="font-semibold text-foreground">✓ Payout: 48 hrs after sale</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/signup" class={linkSecondary + ' w-full justify-center'}>Start Pro</a>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-primary bg-background p-6 relative">
            <span class="absolute -top-3 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-primary px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-primary-foreground">For agencies</span>
            <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">Business</p>
            <p class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold">$99<span class="text-lg font-normal text-muted-foreground">/mo</span></p>
            <ul class="mb-6 space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
              <li>✓ Everything in Pro</li>
              <li class="font-semibold text-foreground">✓ White-label (custom domain)</li>
              <li>✓ API access for integrations</li>
              <li>✓ Phone support</li>
              <li class="font-semibold text-foreground">✓ Payout: daily</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/signup" class={linkPrimary + ' w-full justify-center'}>Start Business</a>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-background p-6">
            <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-muted-foreground">Enterprise</p>
            <p class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold">Custom</p>
            <ul class="mb-6 space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
              <li>✓ Multiple client accounts</li>
              <li>✓ Custom contracts</li>
              <li>✓ SLAs & dedicated support</li>
              <li>✓ Volume pricing</li>
              <li>✓ Onboarding assistance</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="mailto:hello@aizupass.com" class={linkSecondary + ' w-full justify-center'}>Contact us</a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      {/* FAQ */}
      <section class="border-t border-border bg-muted/30 py-20">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6">
          <h2 class="mb-10 text-center text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Agency FAQ</h2>
          <div class="space-y-8 text-sm">
            <div>
              <p class="mb-2 font-semibold">Can we completely white-label this for a client?</p>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">Yes, on the Business tier. Custom domain, your client's logo, their colors in the UI and emails. No AizuPass branding visible to guests or staff.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="mb-2 font-semibold">What happens if the venue has no cell service?</p>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">Staff devices queue check-ins locally. When connection returns, everything syncs. Staff see a live queue count so they know the sync status. No lost data.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="mb-2 font-semibold">Can we assign different staff to different entrances?</p>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">Yes. Create scanner accounts for each door. They all share the same live guest list but only see check-ins from their lane in their session log.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="mb-2 font-semibold">Do we own the guest data after the event?</p>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">Absolutely. Export full attendee lists with check-in timestamps anytime. No platform lock-in, no "contact us to export." Your client's data stays with you.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="mb-2 font-semibold">Can we handle VIP tiers and plus-ones?</p>
              <p class="text-muted-foreground">Yes. Set up multiple guest list tiers with different entry times. Configure plus-one rules per tier. VIP check-ins can trigger a distinct audio chime for door staff.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Final CTA */}
      <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 text-center">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Ready for your next activation?</h2>
        <p class="mb-8 text-lg text-muted-foreground">
          White-label check-in with tiered lists, offline mode, and post-event proof.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-3 sm:flex-row">
          <a href="/signup" class={linkPrimary + ' px-8 py-3 text-base'}>
            Request access
          </a>
          <a href="/" class={linkSecondary + ' px-8 py-3 text-base'}>
            View all plans
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Footer */}
      <footer class="border-t border-border py-8 text-center text-xs text-muted-foreground">
        <p>© {new Date().getFullYear()} AizuPass. Your client's data stays yours.</p>
      </footer>

    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
